data.title: Monta Ellis, Basketball Player
data.meta_description: Monta Ellis stats and bio. Stats averages season by season. Quick access to game by game stats.
data.text:
Monta Ellis - Points

Monta Ellis scores a career high 48 points (2012)

On February 07, 2012, Monta Ellis set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 48 points in Golden State's home loss against Oklahoma City, 116-119. He also had 7 rebounds, 2 assists, 2 steals and 1 block. He shot 15/23 from two, 3/6 from three, shooting at 62.1% from the field. He also shot 9/10 from the free-throw line.

Monta Ellis - Rebounds

Monta Ellis grabs a career high 12 rebounds (2007)

On December 03, 2007, Monta Ellis tied his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 12 rebounds in Golden State's home loss against Orlando, 117-123. He also had 22 points, 7 assists, 5 steals and 1 block.

Monta Ellis - Assists

Monta Ellis gives a career high 17 assists (2013)

On April 12, 2013, Monta Ellis set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 17 assists in Milwaukee's road loss against Atlanta, 109-104. He also had 27 points, 8 rebounds, 5 steals.

Monta Ellis - Steals

Monta Ellis has a career high 7 steals (2010)

On November 05, 2010, Monta Ellis tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 7 steals in Golden State's home win against Utah, 85-78. He also had 23 points, 4 rebounds and 2 assists.

Monta Ellis - Blocks

Monta Ellis blocks a career high 5 shots (2016)

On November 16, 2016, Monta Ellis set his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 5 blocks in Indiana's home win against Cleveland, 103-93. He also had 7 points, 6 rebounds and 4 assists.

Monta Ellis - Efficiency

Monta Ellis records a career high 47 efficiency rating (2011)

On March 11, 2011, Monta Ellis set his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 47 efficiency in Golden State's home win against Orlando, 123-120. He also had 39 points, 6 rebounds and 11 assists.
